uest_.set_version_info(version_info) call updates the tracked version after successful processing. For Delta xDS, the DeltaSubscriptionState maintains per-resource versions through addResourceStateFromServer() calls (lines 229-239 in delta_subscription_state.cc).\n\n6. **Listener Update Dispatch**: When LDS (Listener Discovery Service) resources are received, the LdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate() method in source/common/listener_manager/lds_api.cc (line 49) is invoked by the watch callbacks. This method calls listener_manager_.addOrUpdateListener() (line 100) for each listener resource to apply the configuration to the active listener set.\n\n7. **Cluster Update Dispatch**: When CDS (Cluster Discovery Service) resources are received, the CdsApiImpl::onConfigUpdate() method in source/common/upstream/cds_api_impl.cc (line 40) is invoked. This delegates to helper_.onConfigUpdate() (line 68) to apply cluster configurations to the cluster manager.\n\n8. **Failover Support**: The grpc_mux_failover.h class provides a multiplexing layer that can handle failover to an alternate xDS server, wrapping the base GrpcStream implementation.\n\nThe entire flow ensures that discovered resources are properly validated, decoded, tracked for version consistency, and dispatched to the appropriate Envoy components (listeners, clusters, routes, etc.) for runtime configuration."
